70struct nid_to_digest {
71 int nid;
72 const EVP_MD* (*md_func)(void);
73 const char *short_name;
74 const char *long_name;
75};
76
77static const struct nid_to_digest nid_to_digest_mapping[] = {
78 {NID_md4, EVP_md4, SN_md4, LN_md4},
79 {NID_md5, EVP_md5, SN_md5, LN_md5},
80 {NID_sha1, EVP_sha1, SN_sha1, LN_sha1},
81 {NID_sha224, EVP_sha224, SN_sha224, LN_sha224},
82 {NID_sha256, EVP_sha256, SN_sha256, LN_sha256},
83 {NID_sha384, EVP_sha384, SN_sha384, LN_sha384},
84 {NID_sha512, EVP_sha512, SN_sha512, LN_sha512},
85 {NID_md5_sha1, EVP_md5_sha1, SN_md5_sha1, LN_md5_sha1},
86 // As a remnant of signing |EVP_MD|s, OpenSSL returned the corresponding
87 // hash function when given a signature OID. To avoid unintended lax parsing
88 // of hash OIDs, this is no longer supported for lookup by OID or NID.
89 // Node.js, however, exposes |EVP_get_digestbyname|'s full behavior to
90 // consumers so we retain it there.
91 {NID_undef, EVP_sha1, SN_dsaWithSHA, LN_dsaWithSHA},
92 {NID_undef, EVP_sha1, SN_dsaWithSHA1, LN_dsaWithSHA1},
93 {NID_undef, EVP_sha1, SN_ecdsa_with_SHA1, NULL},
94 {NID_undef, EVP_md5, SN_md5WithRSAEncryption, LN_md5WithRSAEncryption},
95 {NID_undef, EVP_sha1, SN_sha1WithRSAEncryption, LN_sha1WithRSAEncryption},
96 {NID_undef, EVP_sha224, SN_sha224WithRSAEncryption,
97 LN_sha224WithRSAEncryption},
98 {NID_undef, EVP_sha256, SN_sha256WithRSAEncryption,
99 LN_sha256WithRSAEncryption},
100 {NID_undef, EVP_sha384, SN_sha384WithRSAEncryption,
101 LN_sha384WithRSAEncryption},
102 {NID_undef, EVP_sha512, SN_sha512WithRSAEncryption,
103 LN_sha512WithRSAEncryption},
104};
105
106const EVP_MD* EVP_get_digestbynid(int nid) {
107 if (nid == NID_undef) {
108 // Skip the |NID_undef| entries in |nid_to_digest_mapping|.
109 return NULL;
110 }
111
112 for (unsigned i = 0; i < OPENSSL_ARRAY_SIZE(nid_to_digest_mapping); i++) {
113 if (nid_to_digest_mapping[i].nid == nid) {
114 return nid_to_digest_mapping[i].md_func();
115 }
116 }
117
118 return NULL;
119}

121static const struct {
122 uint8_t oid[9];
123 uint8_t oid_len;
124 int nid;
125} kMDOIDs[] = {
126 // 1.2.840.113549.2.4
127 { {0x2a, 0x86, 0x48, 0x86, 0xf7, 0x0d, 0x02, 0x04}, 8, NID_md4 },
128 // 1.2.840.113549.2.5
129 { {0x2a, 0x86, 0x48, 0x86, 0xf7, 0x0d, 0x02, 0x05}, 8, NID_md5 },
130 // 1.3.14.3.2.26
131 { {0x2b, 0x0e, 0x03, 0x02, 0x1a}, 5, NID_sha1 },
132 // 2.16.840.1.101.3.4.2.1
133 { {0x60, 0x86, 0x48, 0x01, 0x65, 0x03, 0x04, 0x02, 0x01}, 9, NID_sha256 },
134 // 2.16.840.1.101.3.4.2.2
135 { {0x60, 0x86, 0x48, 0x01, 0x65, 0x03, 0x04, 0x02, 0x02}, 9, NID_sha384 },
136 // 2.16.840.1.101.3.4.2.3
137 { {0x60, 0x86, 0x48, 0x01, 0x65, 0x03, 0x04, 0x02, 0x03}, 9, NID_sha512 },
138 // 2.16.840.1.101.3.4.2.4
139 { {0x60, 0x86, 0x48, 0x01, 0x65, 0x03, 0x04, 0x02, 0x04}, 9, NID_sha224 },
140};
141
142static const EVP_MD *cbs_to_md(const CBS *cbs) {
143 for (size_t i = 0; i < OPENSSL_ARRAY_SIZE(kMDOIDs); i++) {
144 if (CBS_len(cbs) == kMDOIDs[i].oid_len &&
145 OPENSSL_memcmp(CBS_data(cbs), kMDOIDs[i].oid, kMDOIDs[i].oid_len) ==
146 0) {
147 return EVP_get_digestbynid(kMDOIDs[i].nid);
148 }
149 }
150
151 return NULL;
152}
153
154const EVP_MD *EVP_get_digestbyobj(const ASN1_OBJECT *obj) {
155 // Handle objects with no corresponding OID.
156 if (obj->nid != NID_undef) {
157 return EVP_get_digestbynid(obj->nid);
158 }
159
160 CBS cbs;
161 CBS_init(&cbs, obj->data, obj->length);
162 return cbs_to_md(&cbs);
163}
164
165const EVP_MD *EVP_parse_digest_algorithm(CBS *cbs) {
166 CBS algorithm, oid;
167 if (!CBS_get_asn1(cbs, &algorithm, CBS_ASN1_SEQUENCE) ||
168 !CBS_get_asn1(&algorithm, &oid, CBS_ASN1_OBJECT)) {
169 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(DIGEST, DIGEST_R_DECODE_ERROR);
170 return NULL;
171 }
172
173 const EVP_MD *ret = cbs_to_md(&oid);
174 if (ret == NULL) {
175 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(DIGEST, DIGEST_R_UNKNOWN_HASH);
176 return NULL;
177 }
178
179 // The parameters, if present, must be NULL. Historically, whether the NULL
180 // was included or omitted was not well-specified. When parsing an
181 // AlgorithmIdentifier, we allow both. (Note this code is not used when
182 // verifying RSASSA-PKCS1-v1_5 signatures.)
183 if (CBS_len(&algorithm) > 0) {
184 CBS param;
185 if (!CBS_get_asn1(&algorithm, &param, CBS_ASN1_NULL) ||
186 CBS_len(&param) != 0 ||
187 CBS_len(&algorithm) != 0) {
188 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(DIGEST, DIGEST_R_DECODE_ERROR);
189 return NULL;
190 }
191 }
192
193 return ret;
194}
195
196int EVP_marshal_digest_algorithm(CBB *cbb, const EVP_MD *md) {
197 CBB algorithm, oid, null;
198 if (!CBB_add_asn1(cbb, &algorithm, CBS_ASN1_SEQUENCE) ||
199 !CBB_add_asn1(&algorithm, &oid, CBS_ASN1_OBJECT)) {
200 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(DIGEST, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
201 return 0;
202 }
203
204 int found = 0;
205 int nid = EVP_MD_type(md);
206 for (size_t i = 0; i < OPENSSL_ARRAY_SIZE(kMDOIDs); i++) {
207 if (nid == kMDOIDs[i].nid) {
208 if (!CBB_add_bytes(&oid, kMDOIDs[i].oid, kMDOIDs[i].oid_len)) {
209 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(DIGEST, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
210 return 0;
211 }
212 found = 1;
213 break;
214 }
215 }
216
217 if (!found) {
218 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(DIGEST, DIGEST_R_UNKNOWN_HASH);
219 return 0;
220 }
221
222 if (!CBB_add_asn1(&algorithm, &null, CBS_ASN1_NULL) ||
223 !CBB_flush(cbb)) {
224 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(DIGEST, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
225 return 0;
226 }
227
228 return 1;
229}
230
231const EVP_MD *EVP_get_digestbyname(const char *name) {
232 for (unsigned i = 0; i < OPENSSL_ARRAY_SIZE(nid_to_digest_mapping); i++) {
233 const char *short_name = nid_to_digest_mapping[i].short_name;
234 const char *long_name = nid_to_digest_mapping[i].long_name;
235 if ((short_name && strcmp(short_name, name) == 0) ||
236 (long_name && strcmp(long_name, name) == 0)) {
237 return nid_to_digest_mapping[i].md_func();
238 }
239 }
240
241 return NULL;
242}

244static void blake2b256_init(EVP_MD_CTX *ctx) { BLAKE2B256_Init(ctx->md_data); }
245
246static void blake2b256_update(EVP_MD_CTX *ctx, const void *data, size_t len) {
247 BLAKE2B256_Update(ctx->md_data, data, len);
248}
249
250static void blake2b256_final(EVP_MD_CTX *ctx, uint8_t *md) {
251 BLAKE2B256_Final(md, ctx->md_data);
252}
253
254static const EVP_MD evp_md_blake2b256 = {
255 NID_undef,
256 BLAKE2B256_DIGEST_LENGTH,
257 0,
258 blake2b256_init,
259 blake2b256_update,
260 blake2b256_final,
261 BLAKE2B_CBLOCK,
262 sizeof(BLAKE2B_CTX),
263};
264
265const EVP_MD *EVP_blake2b256(void) { return &evp_md_blake2b256; }
